    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>National Briefing | West: Glaciers Melting More Quickly</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew C. Revkin (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Revkin, Andrew C</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>University of Alaska researchers report state's glaciers are losing 24 cubic miles of ice a year in sharply accelerating meltdown that is contributing to rise in sea levels (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In a sharply accelerating meltdown, Alaska's glaciers are losing 24 cubic miles of ice a year and contributing far more to a slow rise in sea levels than scientists had estimated, a new study in the journal Science concludes. Using airborne laser systems, researchers from the University of Alaska at Fairbanks created the first precise survey of changes in glacier volumes in the region, which has experienced substantial warming in recent years.</p>
        <p>Andrew C. Revkin (NYT)</p>
      </block>
